messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yes, an airplane just went down.
Do you have a location or an intersection?
I think the townhouse is across from P.W. Perry and Flyar Hill, right off of Schoffer School Road.
Can you confirm the intersection?
It's Mallory and Schoffer School Road.
Okay, hold on.
Oh, my God.
Was it a big plane or a small plane?
It didn't look like a real big plane. Medium size.
What's your name?
We could hear the engine noise, my husband and I were in the living room, and we saw it coming down over the trees.
Did the plane explode?
We didn't see an explosion, but there's a parachute type of thing in the tree, orange and white striped.
Do you see any smoke or fire?
No smoke or fire, but we see the parachute thing in the tree.
Okay. We're sending help out there. If you have any more information, call us back.
Okay, sure. Thank you.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Hello, a small aircraft just came down across the street from the nursery here on Schoffer School Road and Flower Hill.
Is it near Terry Laurel Lane?
Just past Terry Laurel. Turn left on Mallory Place.
And your name?
It's Mike. Hurry up.
Sir, we're on the way. Thank you.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
A plane crashed on Mallory and Schoffer School Road.
Yes, we are on the way there.
Okay, thank you.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Yes, an airplane, I think, crashed. A couple of people may have been involved.
Do you see any smoke or fire?
The fuel is leaking on the road.
Is there any smoke or fire?
No smoke, no fire. The operator seems okay.
We're on the way there.
All right. Thank you.
